goals.question: What is the distribution of miles driven per year?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of miles driven per year and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between gas consumption and miles driven?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of gas consumption vs miles driven
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a relationship between gas consumption and miles driven. It can also help us identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the average gas consumption per mile?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of gas per mile
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the average gas consumption per mile and identify any trends over time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of gas consumption?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of gas consumption and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a difference in gas consumption between different sides of the car?
goals.visualization: Box plot of gas consumption by side
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a difference in gas consumption between the sides of the car and if there are any outliers.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven Per Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='miles', y='gas')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between gas consumption and miles driven?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    avg_gas_per_mile = data.groupby('year')['gas_per_mile'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='gas_per_mile', data=avg_gas_per_mile)
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per mile?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Gas Consumption per Mile')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='gas', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['gas'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['gas'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of gas consumption?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='side', y='gas', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a difference in gas consumption between different sides of the car?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Side')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Consumption')
    plt.legend(title='Side', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
